issue.body:
The contract for equals and hashcode is now broken for the following literals

```java
final SimpleValueFactory vf = SimpleValueFactory.getInstance();
Literal v1 = vf.createLiteral("test", "EN");
Literal v2 = vf.createLiteral("test", "en");
v1.equals(v2) // true
v1.hashCode() == v2.hashCode() // false
```
this is caused because equals is using ignore case but the hashcode doesn't. Please lowercase the literal 's language in the setLanguage method.
